:: \ Escape {"position":"4300,700","size":"100,100"}
(if: $attempt is "failed")[Thomas pushes the warehouse owner back. Warehouse owner alerts the guards.]

(if: $stress < 11)[Thomas grabs your arm and pulls you sideways as guards shout. Bullets slam into the table where you were standing seconds ago.

“Move,” he says, low, sharp.

You dive between two stacked containers. The narrow corridor swallows you in shadow. Metal screams as rounds strike the walls, sparks bursting in the dark.

Alexei doesn’t slow down. He knows the layout, or pretends he does.

You cut left. Then right. The containers form a maze, blocking sightlines, swallowing sound.

A forklift sits abandoned ahead.

Thomas shoves it forward. The machine crashes sideways, sealing the passage behind you. Shouts turn distant, confused.

You find a backdoor at the far end of the warehouse, you doesn’t hesitate. You shoulder it open and cold night air rushes in.

The yard is empty. Shadows stretch between the containers, silent and still.

Thomas falls into step beside you, silent. No words. No relief. Only the knowledge that what just happened cannot be undone.

You disappear into the night.

And the world, for a moment, feels unbearably quiet.]

(if: $stress > 10)[Thomas grabs your arm and yanks you aside, but your foot catches a loose plank. You stumble, almost falling as bullets slam the table you had been standing by.

Metal screeches as you land against a container wall. Sparks scatter as a round clips the edge above you.

Alexei moves forward, but the stumble slows him. Thomas shouts something—then slams the forklift forward, but your hesitation nearly blocks the path. The machine tips slightly, a loud metallic crash reverberating through the warehouse.

You finally reach the backdoor, but it sticks briefly under your shoulder. A clatter sounds—distant, but enough to turn heads somewhere in the hangar.

The yard is empty. The alley seems silent. But your heart hammers, ears ringing. Thomas falls beside you, chest heaving, eyes narrowed. You are safe, for now.]

