:: \ Get Ready {"position":"1400,700","size":"100,100"}
You straighten your uniform. Everything is in place. It has to be.
Across from you, Thomas finishes adjusting his gloves, movements precise.

(text-colour:blue)[Thomas:] You’re tense.

(text-colour:lime)[You:] So are you.

Thomas doesn’t deny it.

Your eyes linger on the revolver resting on the table at the corner of the room. You’ve carried it through other nights, other rooms. Not because it was part of the plan, but because plans didn’t always survive contact.

Thomas notices the look.

(text-colour:blue)[Thomas:] You know there is a no-gun policy for this meeting. It works if it stays simple.

(text-colour:lime)[You:] We are not just any soldier. We’re an important part of the Union. Us carrying guns isn’t unusual. It’s a precaution.

Thomas exhales slowly. Not approval—but not refusal.

(text-colour:blue)[Thomas:] There will be a security checkpoint. If they find it, you hand it over. No questions. No consequences.

He meets your eyes.

(text-colour:blue)[Thomas:] But if something goes wrong before that… you’ll be glad you had it.

Nothing feels wrong. Not yet.
Still, that familiar pressure sits in your chest—the sense that tonight isn’t meant to stay simple.

