:: \ Plan {"position":"3700,700","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:red)[Krakov] turns back and takes a look at the documents.

He studies them for a moment, then looks up, unfazed.

(text-colour:red)[Karakov]: Good. This deal will allow us to move decisively. No one will stand in the way for long.

He closes the folder with a soft sound.

(text-colour:red)[Karakov]: The war has lasted long enough. Prolonged conflicts only multiply the dead. I will decide who lives and who doesn’t. And tonight’s agreement ensures we have the tools to enforce that.

A pause.

(text-colour:red)[Karakov]: A single, coordinated action ends it all. After that, there will be no second power. Only us. Only the Union. And this arrangement will make the inescapable end to arrive quicker.

His tone is calm. Almost instructional. But everybody in the warehouse can feel the hunger and the desire of power underlying in his words. Thomas says nothing.

(text-colour:red)[Karakov] turns slightly, addressing the room without raising his voice.

(text-colour:red)[Karakov]: “History will argue about numbers. It always does. What matters is that there will be no one left to argue with us. And these documents ensure the plan will bring the reckoning before they can even react.”

Silence.

(text-colour:blue)[Thomas] finally shifts his gaze. Not to (text-colour:red)[Karakov]. ''To you...''

Eliminating him right then and there might end the war for good, you may never get the chance to be face to face with (text-colour:red)[Karakov] ever again. But if you fail, there is no coming back from it.


